CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 24, 1955, pg. A14, reads: "Car Caroms Off Pole Into Parlor - House Crash - Here is a view of Federal Street and East Jefferson Street where an unidentified driver raced up Federal Street and crashed through the brick wall of Mrs. Ossie Stevenson's home Sunday morning.  The 1954 sedan, owned by Mrs. Delores Stanley of 554 Ridgewood, hit a pole at the left as it came up the hill from town, skidded over to the right in front of the woman in the picture, and finally made an automobile show room in Mrs. Stevenson's home."
TitMainTitle: Federal Street at intersection of East Jefferson Street, with house damaged from car wreck on right, Northside
